The White House Press Secretary issued a statement on Bahrain, expressing President Obama's support for the launch of the National Dialogue in Bahrain. The President commends King Hamad bin Isa al-Khalifa for initiating the dialogue and also praises Al Wifaq, Bahrain's largest opposition group, for joining the dialogue. The statement emphasizes the importance of creating a positive atmosphere for the dialogue process. The United States also welcomes the formation of a commission of inquiry to investigate and report on the recent unrest in Bahrain. The statement highlights that the commission's independent assessment and identification of those responsible will play a crucial role in advancing reconciliation, justice, and peace in Bahrain. As a long-standing partner of Bahrain, the United States believes that respecting the universal rights of the people of Bahrain and implementing reforms that meet their aspirations will enhance the stability of the country.